## Unit 3 Day 8-10: Basic CSS

First, let's explore the fifth lesson in the curriculum. To begin, find your ECS Version 5 curriculum and open to page 111-113.

<a href="http://code.org/ecs#page=111" target="_blank">Access a Digital Copy of the Lesson >></a>


#### Key Concepts

1. Students will be introduced to inline styles and creating an internal style sheet with css so they can  explore using css formatting and style for a web page, while using html to provide the content.

#### Common Difficulties

This lesson introduces css, Cascading Style Sheets.  If you are new to CSS you will need to take some time to learn how to use the different methods for inserting styles to web pages. There are some resources to refer to at [http://www.tizag.com/cssT/](html/css--basic markup) or [http://learn.shayhowe.com/html-css/getting-to-know-css/](http://learn.shayhowe.com/html-css/getting-to-know-css/), w3schools.com, Khan Academy and CodeCademy.

